{"pagelen": 50, "values": [{"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228997.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228997"}}, "parent": {"id": 35228605, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228605.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228605"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "from http://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt\n\n~~~\nThe copyright notices in the Software and this entire statement, including\nthe above license grant, this restriction and the following disclaimer,\nmust be included in all copies of the Software, in whole or in part, and\nall derivative works of the Software, unless such copies or derivative\nworks are solely in the form of machine-executable object code generated by\na source language processor.\n~~~\n\nseems like we need a copy of the boost license in the relevant new files", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>from <a href=\"http://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>The copyright notices in the Software and this entire statement, including\nthe above license grant, this restriction and the following disclaimer,\nmust be included in all copies of the Software, in whole or in part, and\nall derivative works of the Software, unless such copies or derivative\nworks are solely in the form of machine-executable object code generated by\na source language processor.\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>seems like we need a copy of the boost license in the relevant new files</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:43:36.459845+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:43:36.463251+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35228997}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228762.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228762"}}, "parent": {"id": 35228605, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228605.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228605"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "Yeah, that was kind of my thinking, but I wasn't sure if that was allowed here.  If we do go that way, I'll amend the license and add a comment saying where I pulled the code from.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Yeah, that was kind of my thinking, but I wasn't sure if that was allowed here.  If we do go that way, I'll amend the license and add a comment saying where I pulled the code from.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:39:55.670216+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "clalancette", "uuid": "{02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f/048a0933-60ac-4910-a6a5-ed058bdea8eb/128"}}, "nickname": "clalancette", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f"}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:39:55.672836+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35228762}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228605.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228605"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "If the reasons to remove boost don't include its license, can the copyright notice on Filesystem.hh and Filesystem.cc be the boost license?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>If the reasons to remove boost don't include its license, can the copyright notice on Filesystem.hh and Filesystem.cc be the boost license?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:37:31.839942+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Shane Loretz", "uuid": "{656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:684383ab-ac95-4859-a350-4a6f41a94a22/c7a1ebf5-cade-4115-9f26-9d3facb776db/128"}}, "nickname": "Shane Loretz", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:684383ab-ac95-4859-a350-4a6f41a94a22"}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:37:31.843792+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35228605}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228392.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228392"}}, "parent": {"id": 35228122, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228122.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228122"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "It's possible, but I'm doubtful it will work the same way.  In particular, exists() currently works for both files and directories; if std::ofstream::open is mapped down to the open() libc call, it won't work for directories properly I believe.  That being said, I can test it out and see what happens.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>It's possible, but I'm doubtful it will work the same way.  In particular, exists() currently works for both files and directories; if std::ofstream::open is mapped down to the open() libc call, it won't work for directories properly I believe.  That being said, I can test it out and see what happens.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:34:21.465961+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "clalancette", "uuid": "{02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f/048a0933-60ac-4910-a6a5-ed058bdea8eb/128"}}, "nickname": "clalancette", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:34:21.468625+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35228392}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228234.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228234"}}, "parent": {"id": 35227633, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35227633.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35227633"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "I had earlier suggested exactly that, which was more-or-less embedding the SDF files in the library itself without grubbing around in the filesystem for it.  While I still think that has value, we will still need a replacement for boost::filesystem anyway.  For instance, in the code that reads in the URI for the model, we necessarily have to go grubbing around in the filesystem.  Thus, I think embedding the SDF files into the library is actually orthogonal to this.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I had earlier suggested exactly that, which was more-or-less embedding the SDF files in the library itself without grubbing around in the filesystem for it.  While I still think that has value, we will still need a replacement for boost::filesystem anyway.  For instance, in the code that reads in the URI for the model, we necessarily have to go grubbing around in the filesystem.  Thus, I think embedding the SDF files into the library is actually orthogonal to this.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:31:57.076278+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "clalancette", "uuid": "{02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f/048a0933-60ac-4910-a6a5-ed058bdea8eb/128"}}, "nickname": "clalancette", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:31:57.079074+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35228234}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35228122.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35228122"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "Maybe the code for `exists` could be replaced with a call to `std::ofstream::open` followed by checking if the stream has the failbit set?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Maybe the code for <code>exists</code> could be replaced with a call to <code>std::ofstream::open</code> followed by checking if the stream has the failbit set?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:30:07.006988+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Shane Loretz", "uuid": "{656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:684383ab-ac95-4859-a350-4a6f41a94a22/c7a1ebf5-cade-4115-9f26-9d3facb776db/128"}}, "nickname": "Shane Loretz", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:684383ab-ac95-4859-a350-4a6f41a94a22"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:30:07.009473+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35228122}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335/comments/35227633.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335/_/diff#comment-35227633"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}, "content": {"raw": "Maybe we can avoid the license question by changing some logic to not need the filesystem features. If I understand correctly boost::filesystem was used in this file to look for the directories with schema versions. I think it could be eliminated by having CMake create a header will a list of schema versions. \n\nWasn't there also a comment somewhere about including the schema files inside of the libsdformat binary?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Maybe we can avoid the license question by changing some logic to not need the filesystem features. If I understand correctly boost::filesystem was used in this file to look for the directories with schema versions. I think it could be eliminated by having CMake create a header will a list of schema versions. </p>\n<p>Wasn't there also a comment somewhere about including the schema files inside of the libsdformat binary?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-18T18:22:27.292841+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Shane Loretz", "uuid": "{656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B656e3311-aad9-45a1-aaf7-b0ee0e84b287%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:684383ab-ac95-4859-a350-4a6f41a94a22/c7a1ebf5-cade-4115-9f26-9d3facb776db/128"}}, "nickname": "Shane Loretz", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:684383ab-ac95-4859-a350-4a6f41a94a22"}, "inline": {}, "updated_on": "2017-04-18T18:23:26.410752+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 35227633}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"update": {"description": "This is a PR to remove more of boost from sdformat.  This PR is mostly concerned with replacing uses of boost::filesystem in the library.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 potential problems with this PR that I would like to discuss:\r\n\r\n1. If you look closely at Filesystem.cc, most of the Windows code is lifted directly from boost/libs/filesystem, then adapted to fit the sdformat style (along with various other fixes).  I'm not sure how the licensing works in this case; how do we proceed here?\r\n1. There are no tests for Filesystem.cc.  The main reason for this is that I am missing portable versions of some primitives I would need to have reliable tests (change directory, remove directory, etc).  Should I spend time porting those primitives from boost, even though we don't use them in the main code?", "title": "Remove boost 11", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "6b84a7ae5505", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/commit/6b84a7ae5505.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/commits/6b84a7ae5505"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}ts=1606789"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdformat", "full_name": "osrf/sdformat", "uuid": "{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "fa938fccc0e0", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/commit/fa938fccc0e0.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/commits/fa938fccc0e0"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}ts=1606789"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdformat", "full_name": "osrf/sdformat", "uuid": "{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}"}, "branch": {"name": "remove-boost-11"}}, "state": "OPEN", "author": {"display_name": "clalancette", "uuid": "{02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f/048a0933-60ac-4910-a6a5-ed058bdea8eb/128"}}, "nickname": "clalancette", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f"}, "date": "2017-04-18T15:26:47.809892+00:00"}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}, {"update": {"description": "This is a PR to remove more of boost from sdformat.  This PR is mostly concerned with replacing uses of boost::filesystem in the library.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 potential problems with this PR that I would like to discuss:\r\n\r\n1. If you look closely at Filesystem.cc, most of the Windows code is lifted directly from boost/libs/filesystem, then adapted to fit the sdformat style (along with various other fixes).  I'm not sure how the licensing works in this case; how do we proceed here?\r\n1. There are no tests for Filesystem.cc.  The main reason for this is that I am missing portable versions of some primitives I would need to have reliable tests (change directory, remove directory, etc).  Should I spend time porting those primitives from boost, even though we don't use them in the main code?", "title": "Remove boost 11", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "6b84a7ae5505", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/commit/6b84a7ae5505.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/commits/6b84a7ae5505"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}ts=1606789"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdformat", "full_name": "osrf/sdformat", "uuid": "{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}"}, "branch": {"name": "default"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "fa938fccc0e0", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/commit/fa938fccc0e0.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/commits/fa938fccc0e0"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}ts=1606789"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "sdformat", "full_name": "osrf/sdformat", "uuid": "{b6d52f9f-b070-41c0-807c-94af07ea375b}"}, "branch": {"name": "remove-boost-11"}}, "state": "OPEN", "author": {"display_name": "clalancette", "uuid": "{02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B02b311e1-297d-4232-89c4-5485d0a02911%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f/048a0933-60ac-4910-a6a5-ed058bdea8eb/128"}}, "nickname": "clalancette", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ad6ed80b-ec66-45cb-9504-b1094a415b7f"}, "date": "2017-04-18T15:26:47.690205+00:00"}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 335, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/sdformat/pullrequests/335.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/sdformat/pull-requests/335"}}, "title": "Remove boost 11"}}]}